i'll follow up with the infra team -- with 23.07 we now have 3 different deployment modes
1. AI Hub 
2. IB Platform with LLM calling from Refiner (for SaaS or LLM supported sandboxes) 
3. IB Platform without LLM calling from Refiner (for most on-prem customers) 
ib.com (http://ib.com) is probably on (3) right now; need to make this (2) or have another env for this.

BP pr here (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/44917/files)! I'm not sure about why token_usage_stats is missing. It seems like model service code removes that key (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/125be7b235f3959659bfbf4c09d228b17b115322/webserver/api-server/src/py/instabase/api_server_apps/handler/api/v1/model_service.py#L440) from the model result before returning it..
